args:
In Valkaheim, Chelle and Leonidas discuss
various topics, from Aurelius's last words
and the threat of Agito, to disquieting activity
from the Ilian Church. Having realized their
youngest brother is facing dire straits,
Leonidas implores Chelle to help him.
Have we still not ascertained\nPhares's location?
I'm afraid not, Your Highness. Since he\nfled the capital, not a single one of our\nscouts has seen or heard anything.

We have managed to track the movements
of the seventh scion, however. He and his
party appear to be making for the northern
border, presumably to rescue the princess.
He abandoned the capital to go after\nZethia? Just what is he doing...
The waters churn quite violently, hmm?
Tch. Must you slither everywhere you go?
Come now, brother dearest, don't be cruel.
I'd heard you were injured quite severely.\nAre you well?
Heh. Yes, you look as hale as can be.\nIt does my heart well, but I must admit\nto some manner of disappointment.
How excited I was to see my dear, dear\nbrother weakened and wizened by injury!
Enough. Speak your business and begone\nbefore my patience falters.
Yes, yes, I shall get to my point.
You've been keeping secrets, Brother.\nAnd I think it's time to share.
Say, for example, something about the\nfifth scion?
I know you colluded with our father to seal\nhim away in the castle. OUR little brother,\nwhom I have yet to see with my own eyes.
...I did not collude. I took over the watch\nafter our father's death, yes—but it was\npurely out of necessity.
The power of his black mana had only\ngrown more terrible over time. Killing\nhim was no longer an option.
He had been a danger since birth;\nhe entered this world swaddled in\nthat most ebon of mana.
Killing him then would have been the\nbest course for Alberia. But Father did\nnot do so.
Instead, he locked him away in the\ndeepest recesses of the palace.
And now, Phares has freed him in hopes\nof harnessing the Other's power.
Damn him... He has put all of Alberia—no,\nall of the WORLD—at impossible risk.
A power so potent it can produce void\ndragons and consume the Other entirely...
It is no wonder Phares would set his eyes\nupon it.
I have been concerned about his activities\nfor quite some time. As soon as I learn\nwhat he's planning, I shall send word.
All of that said, however, I believe\nthe north requires our more\nimmediate attention.
I presume you've heard tell of the group\nthat has been terrorizing Alberia of late?\nThey call themselves ＂Agito.＂
I've received reports indicating they are\ninvading from the northern border, which\nreminded me of something.
Before Father passed away, he seemed\nterribly afraid of northern Grastaea.
One need only look at where he positioned\nthe two of us, so far north from the capital,\nas proof.
Of course, I haven't the foggiest idea what\nhe might have been afraid of. Perhaps you\nmight know, Brother?
I do not. However, he did broach\na...curious subject with me before\nhis passing.
You are my eldest, Leonidas, and so I must\ntell you this in the event of my death.
I shall not open my ears to such cowardly\nwords from a king, even if that king is\nmy father.

It is precisely because I am king that I
must tell you this. Now, listen well. If the
time should come, you must do all in your
power to protect the people of Alberia.
They have believed in and supported the\nroyal family, and you must never betray\nthem.
And, when the opportunity presents itself,\ngo to Grams in northern Grastaea.
I have nothing further for you now. Should\nyou go at the proper time, you will find\nyour answer. Remember this well.
Grams is the city ruled by the Ilian Church.\nWhat could Father have been talking\nabout...?
Knowing you, you've no doubt sent your\ncats to sniff around already. Have you\ngleaned nothing?
No, not yet. Though I have begun to\nwonder whether the answer may lie\nwith that Nedrick fellow.
...Hmm. It appears the time for my visit\ndraws near.
Then you intend to make for Grams?
Not yet. I shall remain here for the\nmoment to maintain a watchful eye\non both the capital and the north.

With the Other excised, many eyes will
doubtless wander toward the vacant
throne. And Valyx, who maintained the
peace, has left on an expedition.
Mmm, indeed. And what of the Church?
I am aware of their suspicious dealings.\nWe must not show any sign of weakness,\nnow more than ever.
Hee hee. You've been paying close\nattention, I see.
Well, this was an utterly delightful\nrendezvous, but it's time I took\nmy leave.
Oh? Is there something else? Or are you\nso reluctant to be parted from your sister?
Spare me your mockery. I want you to\nprotect {player_name}.
My, my, what a curious development\nthis is! Why would you ask this favor\nof me?
He will be embroiled in tremendous\nhardship in the days ahead.
Your support would be most welcome,\nI think. Besides, would it not behoove\nyou to hold a debt over him?
You speak true, and yet... Is it wise?\nAfter all, we still don't know his true\nidentity.
I know all that I require. He is a man who\ndoes not shy away from the truth—and he\nis my brother, besides.
Eee hee hee! Hearing that alone was worth\nthe trip!
I will think on your request. And now,\none last thing before I depart...
If I'm not mistaken, there is still one\nmember of our family who remains\nin the capital.
I rather suspect we cannot count on him\nfor much, but...you know. Food for thought.\nTa ta!
You mean that fool of a sibling...?
